{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"## Round-3 review surfaced DEEP design issues (not just AC precision) — need decisions before implementation\n\n1. **Write-ahead recovery has a window flaw (blocker).** `recover_pending_bindings` (binding_store.py:450)\n   searches for the `rebar-id:{local_id}` LABEL to reclaim an orphaned create. But that label is planted AFTER\n   `create_issue` (dispatch_one.py:253). A crash in the EXACT window this protocol targets (between create and\n   label) leaves an issue with NO rebar-id label → the label-search recovery CANNOT find it. The mechanism as\n   specified does not close its own target window. DECISION NEEDED: either (a) plant the rebar-id via a create-time\n   field/label that Jira applies atomically with create (verify acli supports labels on create), or (b) recover by\n   a secondary key (summary + a pending-record fingerprint) rather than the post-create label, or (c) accept the\n   residual window and document it. This is a real premise gap in the audit finding.\n2. **`add_comment` dedup marker undefined (blocker).** The per-retry dedup guard needs a marker to search on for\n   comments; there is no comment-marker scheme today. DECISION: define a marker (e.g. a hidden `[rebar-cid:<hash>]`\n   trailer) or scope comment retries out (only guard create, which HAS the rebar-id JQL key).\n3. **`steal()` decision needs a lease-expiry API (blocker).** `__main__.py:500` uses\n   `advisory.check_pass_lock()` → plain bool; it does not expose lease age. To decide steal-vs-exit-3 the held-lock\n   path must read `RefLockState` (`heartbeat_ns` + `lease_secs`, _ref_lock.py) and compute expiry. Add an advisory\n   helper (e.g. `pass_lock_is_expired(repo_root) -> bool`) that reads the state; keep exit 3 for a live lease.\n4. **Manifest tally key**: `recovery_failures` does not exist — the schema uses `mutation_failures`\n   (reconcile.py:1046,1054). Either reuse an existing tally or ADD a defined `recovery_failures` key to the\n   manifest schema (manifest_renderer.py) as an explicit sub-task.\n\nThe non-breaking retry approach (extend `_call_with_retry` for HTTPError 429/5xx, leave acli_rest raw-raise\nunchanged) from round-1/2 remains sound. Items 1-3 above are genuine design decisions the ticket must make before\nit is claimable/implementable — flagging so the continuation resolves them rather than re-discovering them."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783568355145075001,"uuid":"b832610b-4ce0-4346-aadc-bc855790067a"}